Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.23,0:00:11.08,Ange-main,Emperor,0000,0000,0000,,To think that the DRAGON \Nwould launch an attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.08,0:00:13.95,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,This Para-mail... It isn't a DRAGON's, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.33,0:00:17.64,Ange-main,Queen,0000,0000,0000,,It is the Misurugi royal family's \Nduty to Manage the Singulars.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.64,0:00:21.00,Ange-main,Queen,0000,0000,0000,,Mister Julio—no, Your Majesty, please explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.31,0:00:26.46,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,There's no sign whatsoever that \Nthe Dawn Pillar was activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.76,0:00:28.51,Ange-main,Cleric,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense. Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.51,0:00:32.34,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,We must re-establish Arzenal \Nand reinforce it immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.34,0:00:34.58,Ange-main,Emperor,0000,0000,0000,,But we cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.64,0:00:38.80,Ange-main,President,0000,0000,0000,,This machine... it can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.58,0:00:40.72,Ange-main,President,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Villkiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.37,0:00:45.46,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,It should have been destroyed \Nduring the revolt.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.46,0:00:48.81,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,It is the Rosenblum royal \Nfamily's duty to Manage Arzenal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.81,0:00:50.23,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,Why was this neglected?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.23,0:00:54.02,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,The commanding officer\N reported nothing out of the ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.02,0:00:56.90,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,Was she duped by the Normas?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.90,0:00:57.78,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,How incompetent.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.11,0:01:03.00,Ange-main,Cleric,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder a princess could so\N easily be abducted by the Norma.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.65,0:01:08.08,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,I won't allow Misty to be insulted,\N not even by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.08,0:01:10.17,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,Be calm, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.17,0:01:11.67,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,Silence, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.67,0:01:15.88,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,It was your sister that took my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.07,0:01:19.30,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,That thing is no longer my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.30,0:01:21.38,Ange-main,Cleric,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think we'll accept such an excuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.38,0:01:23.26,Ange-main,Cleric,0000,0000,0000,,You family of criminals...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.26,0:01:24.57,Ange-main,Queen,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.57,0:01:28.30,Ange-main,Queen,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, we need to\N discuss how we'll protect the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.84,0:01:30.98,Ange-main,President,0000,0000,0000,,Without the Norma to rely on,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.98,0:01:34.03,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,will we humans have to do battle ourselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.40,0:01:41.28,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,You're all hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.13,0:01:44.54,Ange-main,King,0000,0000,0000,,Embryo-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.39,0:01:51.17,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Completely hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.47,0:03:26.48,Ange-EpTitle,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(464,517)}Her Right Arm's Past
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.68,0:03:26.48,Ange-top,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,We have two options.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.48,0:03:29.60,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,One, surrender unconditionally to the DRAGONs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.08,0:03:34.06,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Two, wipe out the DRAGONs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.35,0:03:35.65,Ange-main,Queen,0000,0000,0000,,That's unthinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.81,0:03:39.57,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Then three, rebuild the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.31,0:03:43.91,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Destroy it all, and reset it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.22,0:03:48.83,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Kill the pests, replace the dirt,\N and purify the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.13,0:03:51.30,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,Destroy and rebuild it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:54.04,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,Can that be done?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.53,0:03:58.75,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,If we can obtain all the \NRagna-mail and mail riders, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.75,0:04:01.77,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,Brilliant! Let's rebuild.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.77,0:04:03.01,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,Immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.32,0:04:05.64,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,It was all a mistake in the first place...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.64,0:04:10.82,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,That the wretched Norma exist, \Nand that the world needs them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.15,0:04:12.18,Ange-main,Cleric,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.18,0:04:15.43,Ange-main,Cleric,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying we should abandon \Nall the world's development?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.43,0:04:18.00,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,Can you propose another way?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.80,0:04:22.15,Ange-main,Emperor,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose that is the only way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.50,0:04:25.45,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Here. Use the tools in the yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.15,0:04:28.41,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Julio-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.41,0:04:31.20,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me, Embryo-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.32,0:04:38.65,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving, Riza.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.45,0:04:45.43,Ange-main,Tusk,0000,0000,0000,,They're playing a dangerous hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.70,0:04:49.10,Ange-main,Tusk,0000,0000,0000,,Destroy everything and rebuild, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.48,0:04:50.63,Ange-main,Tusk,0000,0000,0000,,I have to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.06,0:05:22.44,Ange-main,Emma,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.25,0:05:28.64,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,So these are all the survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.23,0:05:30.60,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Who has command experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.79,0:05:35.98,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,We're regrouping and\N reassigning all Para-mail troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.31,0:05:38.19,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Hilda will be the interim captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:39.94,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Ersha and Vivian, you're her lieutenants.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.94,0:05:41.22,Ange-main,Rosalie,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.22,0:05:43.01,Ange-main,Rosalie,0000,0000,0000,,She's a deserter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.01,0:05:45.14,Ange-main,Rosalie,0000,0000,0000,,You're making a deserter a captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.14,0:05:46.86,Ange-main,Chris,0000,0000,0000,,Why not Salia?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.33,0:05:51.41,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,She's in detention for violating orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.35,0:05:54.93,Ange-main,Hilda,0000,0000,0000,,If you have a problem with me, \Nwhy don't you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.93,0:05:57.34,Ange-main,Rosalie,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's the commander's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.34,0:05:59.52,Ange-main,Rosalie,0000,0000,0000,,I have no choice, so I'll deal with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.52,0:06:00.88,Ange-main,Rosalie,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Chris?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.41,0:06:07.59,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Para-mail troops are to organize \Nthemselves and then stand on alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.07,0:06:09.33,Ange-main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.61,0:06:18.22,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Destroy and rebuild, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.58,0:06:19.35,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.11,0:06:22.71,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,My detention is over, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.01,0:06:23.77,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.06,0:06:25.89,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell me everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.89,0:06:26.94,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,You promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.41,0:06:29.86,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Now, when we're busy as hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.11,0:06:33.17,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think saved everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.61,0:06:35.89,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.89,0:06:37.41,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,But ditch the maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.23,0:06:42.51,Ange-main,Hilda,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Where are you going, Ange?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.51,0:06:44.92,Ange-main,Hilda,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! When we've got to hustle, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.92,0:06:47.26,Ange-main,Ersha,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, where's Vivi-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.13,0:06:55.18,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:06:57.80,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,I fell?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.80,0:06:58.68,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.27,0:07:01.35,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! I overslept.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.62,0:07:06.32,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Why in the bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.32,0:07:09.07,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Secrets should be shared \Nwhen completely exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.59,0:07:12.09,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do you want to hear first?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.09,0:07:13.57,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Everything, from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.79,0:07:15.57,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,About the DRAGONs, about that woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.96,0:07:18.73,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,About my Para-mail, and my mother's song.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.09,0:07:21.39,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Your relationship with Tusk...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.39,0:07:22.33,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.57,0:07:24.67,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.28,0:07:29.38,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Long, long ago, there was God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.55,0:07:34.27,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,God was tired of seeing war \Nafter war, and of seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.27,0:07:36.58,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the earth in ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.43,0:07:38.97,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.41,0:07:41.85,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Everything, from the beginning. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.28,0:07:47.15,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Peace, friendship, equality...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.15,0:07:50.77,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,We speak of beautiful things, \Nbut the history of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.77,0:07:54.24,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,humanity is a cycle of war,\N hatred and prejudice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.58,0:07:56.79,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,That is the true nature of human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.79,0:07:59.99,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Something had to be done, \Nor they would eventually perish.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.79,0:08:04.58,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,So, God decided to create anew.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.88,0:08:06.59,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,A new humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.40,0:08:11.13,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,A gentle, intelligent humanity\N with no desire for conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.82,0:08:13.96,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,The advanced information technology, Mana,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.96,0:08:17.23,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,allowed things to be \Nmanipulated with the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.27,0:08:21.92,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,This ended suffering of all kinds,\Nand granted wishes of all kinds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.92,0:08:26.39,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,It led to the creation of an ideal state,\N where anything could be had.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.72,0:08:31.82,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,All that was left to do was to \Nwatch over humanity's development.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.36,0:08:34.00,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,At least, that was the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.28,0:08:37.99,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,But there they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.48,0:08:40.48,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how often the system was rebuilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.48,0:08:43.46,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,some female babies couldn't use Mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.71,0:08:46.61,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,It was a mutation that expressed an old gene.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.80,0:08:51.88,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,This mutation led to fear among the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.66,0:08:58.05,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,But God decided to take \Nadvantage of the mutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.75,0:09:01.56,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,He propagated the notion that these girls
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.56,0:09:05.67,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,had rejected the world.\N That they were antisocial monsters,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.67,0:09:07.90,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,bent on destroying it... Normas.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.55,0:09:12.61,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,The world united for the\N sake of dealing with the Norma.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.09,0:09:16.25,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,People took solace in knowing\N who to discriminate against,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.25,0:09:17.92,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and there was stability.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.71,0:09:21.67,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Sacrifices, scapegoats, necessary evils...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:24.46,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Call us whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.46,0:09:28.31,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,We were also just created...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.68,0:09:30.76,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,To bring stability to the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.76,0:09:32.71,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,To be discriminated against.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.99,0:09:36.35,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? At a loss for words?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.15,0:09:39.14,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,It's all just so silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.38,0:09:42.89,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed you could come \Nup with such a stupid story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.21,0:09:45.64,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I heard it straight from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.64,0:09:48.27,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,So, there's more, isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.27,0:09:49.98,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to hurry me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.29,0:09:53.89,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,And so the world of Mana became stable,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.89,0:09:57.14,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and it seemed like the beginning \Nof a prosperous history.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.66,0:10:02.94,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,But some people wouldn't allow that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.76,0:10:05.30,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,The Ancient People.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.80,0:10:11.25,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Outcast survivors of the old \Nhumanity that couldn't use Mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.15,0:10:15.14,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,They challenged God many \Ntimes in order to reclaim
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.14,0:10:17.25,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,their place in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.10,0:10:22.55,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,After a long war, and grieving \Nfor their fallen comrades,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.93,0:10:24.89,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,they finally captured it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.55,0:10:27.01,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,The weapon of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.01,0:10:28.24,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Ragna-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.98,0:10:32.15,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,A mechanical angel of \Ndestruction and creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.53,0:10:35.40,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,The ultimate weapon that\N was the Para-mail's prototype.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.57,0:10:38.11,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Villkiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.58,0:10:41.42,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,With it, they could fight just as well God.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.27,0:10:44.66,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,The Ancient People boarded the Villkiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.67,0:10:48.97,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,But they couldn't handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.67,0:10:53.52,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,It was locked...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:56.73,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,So that mere insects couldn't use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.04,0:11:01.19,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,With a mere handful of survivors,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.19,0:11:04.16,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the Ancient People had only \Nto wait for their own demise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.29,0:11:09.02,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,That's when they found out that \NNormas sent off to the edge
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.02,0:11:12.82,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,of the earth were being forced to\N fight the DRAGONs with Para-mails.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.01,0:11:16.08,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,They set off for Arzenal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.57,0:11:19.28,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,There was contact...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.00,0:11:22.14,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Between the Ancient People and the Norma,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.14,0:11:24.28,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,the two abandoned humanities.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.24,0:11:28.03,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,They became allies, and made preparations
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.64,0:11:31.10,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,for when one would \Nemerge to open the lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.07,0:11:34.52,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,And she finally arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.31,0:11:38.30,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Alektra Maria von Loewenherz.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.78,0:11:42.16,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,The first Norma born of royal blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.87,0:11:52.65,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Alektra Maria von Loewenherz...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.65,0:11:54.17,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.50,0:11:57.86,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I think she was First \NPrincess of the Galia Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.13,0:12:00.63,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I heard she fell ill\N and died when she was ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.47,0:12:03.82,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,It was discovered\N that she was a Norma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.88,0:12:09.91,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,She got thrown into Arzenal, \Nand she fell into despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.27,0:12:16.77,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,But her royal blood and royal ring\N unlocked the Villkiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.61,0:12:23.07,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Many came to her side.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.00,0:12:28.46,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Soldiers to protect the Villkiss, \Nand armorsmiths to repair it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.46,0:12:30.39,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Doctors, weapons makers, dogs...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.99,0:12:36.06,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,It was the beginning of the revolt \Nof the abandoned, of Libertus.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.92,0:12:40.94,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,In the pits of hell,\N I and the others found our calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.94,0:12:45.95,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,To destroy this made-up, piece-of-shit world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.80,0:12:49.66,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,But I wasn't good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.55,0:12:52.12,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,I lost everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.12,0:12:56.49,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,The ring, my friends, my right arm... everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.48,0:13:00.99,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't let Libertus end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.59,0:13:03.55,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Not with so many dead friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.46,0:13:07.72,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,That's when you showed up, Ange.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.70,0:13:13.43,Ange-main,Salia,0000,0000,0000,,Jill, you liar...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.60,0:13:16.81,Ange-main,Salia,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.69,0:13:21.98,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,The Villkiss's last lock is open.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.98,0:13:25.55,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to destroy it, Ange.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.01,0:13:27.91,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,This world, with that song.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.06,0:13:32.33,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,So you brought back my ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.60,0:13:33.50,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.85,0:13:37.54,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,You kept me alive for Libertus?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.03,0:13:39.24,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.54,0:13:42.67,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,I needed you to become stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.50,0:13:45.92,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Alektra, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.07,0:13:48.86,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I'm grateful to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.76,0:13:58.10,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you, I learned how spoiled, \Npampered and sheltered I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.10,0:14:01.77,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,So my answer is, "No."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.55,0:14:03.48,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.48,0:14:09.20,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Even if everything you say about \NGod and Libertus is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.65,0:14:12.24,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,my path is my own to choose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.63,0:14:15.97,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how glorious the duty,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.38,0:14:19.71,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see things with my own \Neyes and decide for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.16,0:14:22.63,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let anyone make me do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.63,0:14:25.76,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,So you won't join Libertus?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.34,0:14:27.59,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I don't hate it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.13,0:14:32.10,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Killing DRAGONs, making money, \Nand buying what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.67,0:14:34.18,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I don't hate my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.61,0:14:35.56,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.26,0:14:41.36,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, in that story...\NYou never mentioned the DRAGONs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.87,0:14:46.94,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,I feel taller.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.37,0:14:49.36,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Is it my growth spurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:51.99,Ange-main,Emma,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't I connect?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.45,0:14:54.66,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's Officer Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.13,0:14:56.57,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.59,0:15:02.53,Ange-main,Emma,0000,0000,0000,,It's Officer Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:06.43,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.92,0:15:08.30,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.48,0:15:16.34,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Is this me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.34,0:15:17.77,Ange-main,Pamela,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.61,0:15:28.90,Ange-main,Pamela,0000,0000,0000,,All units, type one battle formation!\N It's a DRAGON!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.90,0:15:31.61,Ange-main,Pamela,0000,0000,0000,,There's a survivor in the base!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.96,0:15:34.12,Ange-main,Pamela,0000,0000,0000,,Rosalie and Chris will cover the residential area.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.12,0:15:35.78,Ange-main,Pamela,0000,0000,0000,,Ange and I will cover the maintenance deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.35,0:15:39.41,Ange-main,Pamela,0000,0000,0000,,Ersha, let Salia out and search Jasmine Mall.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.38,0:15:41.37,Ange-main,Ersha,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.61,0:15:43.46,Ange-main,Hilda,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of you stand guard here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.46,0:15:44.47,Ange-main,Hilda,0000,0000,0000,,Vivian.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.47,0:15:45.63,Ange-main,Hilda,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Vivian?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.90,0:15:48.09,Ange-main,Ersha,0000,0000,0000,,She's not in her room, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.08,0:15:50.30,Ange-main,Momoka,0000,0000,0000,,Angelise-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.30,0:15:51.26,Ange-main,Hilda,0000,0000,0000,,You're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.26,0:15:52.47,Ange-main,Hilda,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.04,0:15:55.76,Ange-main,Hilda,0000,0000,0000,,Good! All units, go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.76,0:15:57.13,Ange-main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.53,0:16:00.04,Ange-main,Momoka,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Angelise-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.82,0:16:04.98,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Maggie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.33,0:16:07.15,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Get all the inhibitor you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.31,0:16:09.32,Ange-main,Maggie,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.76,0:16:18.87,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.31,0:16:22.25,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,How did this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.13,0:16:29.96,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it, it's curry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.20,0:16:32.24,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Time to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.24,0:16:33.13,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.01,0:16:36.01,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.01,0:16:38.89,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's me that's weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.62,0:16:41.67,Ange-main,Ersha,0000,0000,0000,,There it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.45,0:16:44.42,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Salia, Ersha.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.95,0:16:53.11,Ange-main,Ersha,0000,0000,0000,,Go after it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.48,0:17:13.63,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.18,0:17:28.24,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,The El Laguna hourglass that does not turn
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.98,0:17:29.54,Ange-internal/narrator,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}How does it know this song?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.77,0:17:34.90,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Time does not flow from it, lu la la li la
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.10,0:17:43.22,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,The flames of countless lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.22,0:17:50.00,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Fall through and become stars
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.84,0:17:47.00,Ange-overlap,Hilda,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What's that idiot doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.86,0:17:50.34,Ange-overlap,Maggie,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Is she trying to kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.34,0:17:51.78,Ange-overlap,Maggie,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.66,0:17:57.21,Ange-main,Maggie,0000,0000,0000,,They fly beautifully,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.21,0:18:08.06,Ange-main,Maggie,0000,0000,0000,,And fade away in the \Ncradle of life and death
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.30,0:18:03.10,Ange-overlap,Salia,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Ange!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.63,0:18:04.71,Ange-overlap,Salia,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Step away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.15,0:18:08.11,Ange-overlap,Salia,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Jill.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.85,0:18:19.49,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Quiz time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.88,0:18:23.08,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,What's a DRAGON, even though it's human?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.83,0:18:28.74,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.35,0:18:31.28,Ange-main,,0000,0000,0000,,A human, even though it's a DRAGON?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.66,0:18:32.67,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.07,0:18:34.16,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.71,0:18:36.92,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.31,0:18:40.51,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I got it. It's Vivian.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.06,0:18:43.14,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Vivian.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.29,0:18:56.86,Ange-main,Momoka,0000,0000,0000,,Angelise-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.86,0:18:59.78,Ange-main,Maggie,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.78,0:19:03.28,Ange-main,Chris,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I saw Vivian \Ncome out of the DRAGON...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.53,0:19:18.78,Ange-flashback,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,What's a DRAGON, even though it's human?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.67,0:19:22.89,Ange-flashback,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,A human, even though it's a DRAGON? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.84,0:19:25.78,Ange-main,Momoka,0000,0000,0000,,Angelise-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.72,0:19:37.25,Ange-main,Jasmine,0000,0000,0000,,Stay away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.58,0:19:50.93,Ange-main,Hilda,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.39,0:19:55.21,Ange-main,Ersha,0000,0000,0000,,What are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.55,0:19:57.66,Ange-main,Maggie,0000,0000,0000,,DRAGONs, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.93,0:20:00.22,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.48,0:20:02.13,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,You know how the story goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.57,0:20:08.52,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,"The monster was human all along."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.73,0:20:27.66,Ange-main,Momoka,0000,0000,0000,,Angelise-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.51,0:20:32.58,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I was killing humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.63,0:20:34.93,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,With these hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.55,0:20:36.67,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,With these hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.09,0:20:39.84,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you liked your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.84,0:20:43.55,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Killing DRAGONs and making money.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.39,0:20:46.05,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,Go to hell, bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.49,0:20:48.45,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I won't use the Villkiss anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.45,0:20:50.22,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I won't kill DRAGONs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.22,0:20:51.93,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,To hell with Libertus!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.21,0:20:57.86,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Fine with me, if you want to \Nlive and die as God's pet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.50,0:21:06.07,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,God, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.84,0:21:12.76,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,I've never called myself that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.76,0:21:17.21,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Though it may be appropriate,\N in the sense that I'm a creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.88,0:21:21.13,Ange-main,Jill,0000,0000,0000,,Embryo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.92,0:21:24.99,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,You're beautiful when you're angry, Alektra.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.50,0:21:27.87,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Or are you Commander Jill now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.98,0:21:31.31,Ange-main,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.52,0:21:38.98,Ange-announcer,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,This is the International Rescue Fleet \Nof the Norma Administration Board.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.83,0:21:44.57,Ange-announcer,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Normas, thank you for your \Ngood work fighting the DRAGONs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.93,0:21:48.00,Ange-announcer,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,We will hereby begin your rescue.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.64,0:21:53.86,Ange-announcer,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,We have plenty of water, \Nclothing, and warm food.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.36,0:21:57.79,Ange-announcer,Embryo,0000,0000,0000,,Please abandon your weapons \Nand prepare for evacuation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.48,0:22:04.83,Ange-main,Julio,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to our final reunion, Angelise.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.92,0:23:29.05,next episode preview,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,519)}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.13,0:23:30.00,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,I'm totally fine with Vivian being a DRAGON.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.00,0:23:31.55,Ange-main,Vivian,0000,0000,0000,,You never change, Ange!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.55,0:23:33.64,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,But that song is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.64,0:23:35.80,Ange-main,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to have to pay for singing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.80,0:23:36.87,Ange-top,Ange,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be 700 million.
